{"id": "2026-07-07-news-bern-and-the-cantons-weigh-scrapping-the-mandato", "date": "2026-07-07", "stream": "news", "headline": "Bern and the cantons weigh scrapping the mandatory three hours of weekly school sport", "summary": "Under project Entflechtung 27 (now in consultation), Bern and the cantons propose lifting the compulsory 3h/week school sport; teachers and sport federations object.", "url": "https://www.srf.ch/news/schweiz/edk-gegen-sportlehrer-wird-schulsport-zum-wahlfach-lehrer-und-fachleute-laufen-sturm", "source_domain": "srf.ch", "tier": "T2", "tags": [], "topics": ["switzerland", "politics"], "importance": 2, "display_body": "Three hours of physical education a week are currently compulsory in Swiss schools. Under Entflechtung 27 — a federal-cantonal project to re-sort who pays for and decides on various public tasks, now in its consultation phase — that obligation would be lifted, with the conference of cantonal education directors (EDK) telling SRF it sees no problem because cantonal curricula adequately and conclusively cover sport. Teachers and sport federations are pushing back hard: PE teacher Stefan Frei warns that dropping the guarantee makes sport a de facto elective and would worsen an already-visible rise in childhood inactivity, motor deficits and children who cannot swim, especially in cash-strapped cantons tempted to trim. Associations, cities and communes can file positions until Fri 10 July; a first decision is expected in the autumn.", "why": "", "thread_id": "2026-07-07-news-bern-and-the-cantons-weigh-scrapping-the-mandato", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-07", "event_date": "2026-07-07", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": ""}
{"id": "2026-07-07-news-lausanne-police-discrimination-le-temps-traces-h", "date": "2026-07-07", "stream": "news", "headline": "Lausanne police discrimination: Le Temps traces how officers derailed", "summary": "Le Temps analyses the mechanisms behind the Lausanne police WhatsApp scandal, where officers traded racist and hypersexualised messages for years.", "url": "https://www.letemps.ch/articles/hypersexualisation-et-propos-racistes-comment-des-policiers-lausannois-ont-deraille", "source_domain": "letemps.ch", "tier": "T2", "tags": ["single-source"], "topics": ["switzerland"], "importance": 1, "display_body": "In a follow-up to its reporting on two WhatsApp groups where Lausanne officers traded racist and hypersexualised messages for years, Le Temps examines the mechanisms behind the scandal — the psychological toll of frontline policing that normalises inappropriate language, thin training in deconstructing racist biases, and an institution that failed to stop dysfunctional behaviour reproducing, including by not dismissing officers criminally convicted over police-violence cases. The piece is an analysis rather than a fresh disclosure.", "why": "", "thread_id": "2026-07-07-news-lausanne-police-discrimination-le-temps-traces-h", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-07", "event_date": "2026-07-07", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": ""}
{"id": "2026-07-07-news-nato-s-summit-opens-in-ankara-with-defence-spend", "date": "2026-07-07", "stream": "news", "headline": "NATO's summit opens in Ankara, with defence spending and Ukraine dominating the agenda", "summary": "NATO's two-day summit opened in Ankara on 7 July; Trump presses allies on defence budgets, Zelensky to meet Trump bilaterally on 8 July to seek Patriots.", "url": "https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/7/7/nato-summit-begins-who-is-attending-and-what-is-at-stake", "source_domain": "aljazeera.com", "tier": "T2", "tags": [], "topics": ["geopolitics"], "importance": 3, "display_body": "Leaders of all 32 members convened in Turkey on Tue 7 July for the two-day summit, with President Trump renewing pressure on allies over military budgets; European states are expected to answer with billions in new defence contracts, translating last year's pledge (a 5%-of-GDP target — 3.5% on the military by 2035 plus 1.5% on broader security) into actual capability. Ukraine's Volodymyr Zelensky and South Korea's Lee Jae-myung attend as non-members; Zelensky will meet Trump one-on-one on Wed 8 July to press for more Patriot air-defence systems. Syria's new president Ahmed al-Sharaa is also slated for a bilateral with Trump in Ankara. Analysts are split on whether the summit marks the alliance's renewal or exposes its strains.", "why": "", "thread_id": "2026-07-06-news-nato-leaders-convene-in-ankara-as-trump-prepares", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-06", "event_date": "2026-07-07", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": ""}
{"id": "2026-07-07-news-iran-s-revolutionary-guards-fire-missiles-at-two", "date": "2026-07-07", "stream": "news", "headline": "Iran's Revolutionary Guards fire missiles at two ships in the Strait of Hormuz", "summary": "At least two commercial ships were struck by Iranian missiles near Limah, Oman, overnight into 7 July; an LNG tanker caught fire, Brent rose toward $73, and a recent ceasefire in the strait unravelled.", "url": "https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/7/7/tanker-on-fire-off-coast-of-oman-after-being-hit-by-projectile", "source_domain": "aljazeera.com", "tier": "T2", "tags": [], "topics": ["geopolitics", "economy"], "importance": 2, "display_body": "At least two commercial vessels were struck by missiles overnight into Tue 7 July near Limah, Oman, at the mouth of the strait through which roughly a fifth of the world's oil and gas moved before this year's US-Israel war on Iran; a liquefied-natural-gas (LNG) tanker — reported to be the Qatari-linked Al Rekayyat — caught fire in its engine room with all crew safe. Iran's state broadcaster said a tanker was targeted for crossing with US Navy support after ignoring warnings but stopped short of a direct claim; US officials told Axios the IRGC fired the missiles. The attacks unravel a memorandum signed under three weeks ago in which Iran agreed to halt strikes in the strait, and land just as a one-week US-Iran pause expired with talks concluding last week without progress. Brent crude rose toward $73 a barrel.", "why": "", "thread_id": "2026-07-07-news-iran-s-revolutionary-guards-fire-missiles-at-two", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-07", "event_date": "2026-07-07", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": ""}
{"id": "2026-07-07-news-two-bombs-go-off-in-damascus-during-macron-s-vis", "date": "2026-07-07", "stream": "news", "headline": "Two bombs go off in Damascus during Macron's visit, wounding at least 18", "summary": "Two IEDs detonated in central Damascus on 7 July as Macron visited Syria for talks with al-Sharaa; 18 were wounded but the visit continued.", "url": "https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/7/7/explosions-heard-in-syrias-damascus", "source_domain": "aljazeera.com", "tier": "T2", "tags": [], "topics": ["geopolitics"], "importance": 2, "display_body": "Two improvised explosive devices detonated in central Damascus on Tue 7 July as French President Emmanuel Macron visited Syria for talks with President Ahmed al-Sharaa; Syria's interior ministry, via state agency SANA, said 18 people including four police officers were hurt. One device was planted in a roadside car, the other hidden in a rubbish container, near the tourism ministry and a hotel where Macron had been due to stay. Macron's office said he did not hear the blasts and the visit — the first by a European leader since Bashar al-Assad's fall in late 2024 — continued as planned. Authorities called it a criminal act and opened an investigation.", "why": "", "thread_id": "2026-07-07-news-two-bombs-go-off-in-damascus-during-macron-s-vis", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-07", "event_date": "2026-07-07", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": ""}
{"id": "2026-07-07-news-france-s-appeal-court-rules-tuesday-on-marine-le", "date": "2026-07-07", "stream": "news", "headline": "France's appeal court rules Tuesday on Marine Le Pen, a verdict that could end her 2027 bid", "summary": "The Paris Court of Appeal is due on 7 July to rule on Le Pen's EU-funds conviction; upholding the five-year ban would bar her from the April 2027 presidential race.", "url": "https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/7/7/frances-court-of-appeal-to-rule-on-le-pen-conviction-what-its-all-about", "source_domain": "aljazeera.com", "tier": "T2", "tags": [], "topics": ["politics"], "importance": 2, "display_body": "The Paris Court of Appeal is due Tue 7 July to decide whether to uphold Le Pen's 2025 conviction for misusing 2.9m euros of European Parliament funds to pay National Rally staff between 2004 and 2016. If it confirms the five-year ban from public office, the far-right frontrunner would be barred from the April 2027 presidential race — likely handing the candidacy to her 30-year-old protege Jordan Bardella. Le Pen has said she will not run if merely fitted with an electronic bracelet but prevented from campaigning freely, and can still appeal to the Court of Cassation. Legal experts view an outright acquittal as unlikely.", "why": "", "thread_id": "2026-07-07-news-france-s-appeal-court-rules-tuesday-on-marine-le", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-07", "event_date": "2026-07-07", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": ""}
{"id": "2026-07-07-news-ukraine-sends-430-drones-toward-moscow-after-rus", "date": "2026-07-07", "stream": "news", "headline": "Ukraine sends 430+ drones toward Moscow after Russian strikes kill at least 28", "summary": "Russian strikes on Kyiv, its region and Sumy killed at least 28 on 6 July; Ukraine launched 430+ drones toward Moscow overnight and a missile strike killed one in Belgorod.", "url": "https://www.letemps.ch/articles/en-direct-guerre-en-ukraine-une-personne-tuee-dans-la-region-russe-de-belgorod-en-amont-du-sommet-de-l-otan", "source_domain": "letemps.ch", "tier": "T2", "tags": [], "topics": ["geopolitics"], "importance": 2, "display_body": "Russian bombardments of Kyiv, its region and Sumy on Mon 6 July killed at least 28 people and wounded around a hundred — less than a week after the deadly 1-2 July barrage on the capital. In response Ukraine launched more than 430 drones toward Moscow overnight into Tue 7 July, most downed by air defences (36 destroyed on the capital's approaches, per Mayor Sobyanin), and repeated missile strikes on Russia's Belgorod region killed one civilian. The exchange sets the backdrop for the NATO summit, where Zelensky will press for more interceptors.", "why": "", "thread_id": "2026-05-20-cyber-papers-russia-ukraine-largest-aerial-campaign-of-the-wa", "first_seen_date": "2026-05-20", "event_date": "2026-07-06", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": ""}
{"id": "2026-07-07-news-cuba-hit-by-its-third-nationwide-blackout-in-und", "date": "2026-07-07", "stream": "news", "headline": "Cuba hit by its third nationwide blackout in under six months", "summary": "Cuba's grid collapsed nationwide on 6 July, the third total outage in under six months, as fuel reserves dwindle under a US blockade.", "url": "https://www.letemps.ch/articles/sous-blocus-petrolier-americain-cuba-s-efforce-de-retablir-son-reseau-electrique", "source_domain": "letemps.ch", "tier": "T2", "tags": [], "topics": ["world", "economy"], "importance": 1, "display_body": "Cuba's power grid collapsed across the island of nearly 10 million on Mon 6 July, the third total outage in less than six months, as fuel reserves dwindle under a US blockade; the fuel shortage indisputably complicates restoring the grid, the energy ministry's electricity director told state TV, and by late afternoon the operator could meet just 1% of Havana's demand while prioritising hospitals. Washington has let only one oil tanker through since January, and President Diaz-Canel accused the US of trying to incite social unrest by strangling Cuba's fuel supply.", "why": "", "thread_id": "2026-07-07-news-cuba-hit-by-its-third-nationwide-blackout-of-the", "first_seen_date": "2026-07-07", "event_date": "2026-07-06", "embedding_model": "bge-m3", "emb": ""}
